Function Reference/wp blacklist check « WordPress Codex
-----------

Determines comment contain blacklisted characters or words.

Usage
-----

` <?php wp_blacklist_check($author, $email, $url, $comment, $user_ip, $user_agent); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$author` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required??*) The author of the comment
    Default: *None*

 `$email` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) The email address of the comment author
    Default: *None*

 `$url` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) The website address of the comment author
    Default: *None*

 `$comment` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) The content text of the comment
    Default: *None*

 `$user_ip` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) The IP address of the comment author
    Default: *None*

 `$user_agent` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*??*) The user agent of the comment author's browser. (or sometimes
    of the spamming robot)
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(boolean)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   True if comment contains blacklisted content, false if comment does
    not

Examples
